ldozed of fox new house showing again why lights phone interview". This makes it almost impossible for nonnative English speakers, specifically those with Chinese or Spanish accents to use these voice assistants.%0a%3c %0a%3c The solution is not easy. Since there are so many variations in nonnative English speech as compared to standard American English, engineers at Google and Amazon as well as linguists working with these technologies, it is harder to train the speakers to recognize these accents. A study found a correlation between diversity in voice data and being able to understand more accents. Since the dataset is not diverse enough when it comes to nonnative English accents, the speakers were not able to recognize them.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
